scene.message:
Elly: Well, Kuroori?{wait_fr:30}{nl}
Have you found{nl}
anything out?{waitkey}{ret}

Kuroori: Hehehe...{nl}
Of course, Kirishima.{waitkey}{clearbox}This is{wait_fr:30}.{wait_fr:30}.{wait_fr:30}...{wait_fr:30}.{wait_fr:30}{nl}
no work of a cold front!{waitkey}No, really.{waitkey}{ret}

Kuroori: Eek~ sorry...{waitkey}{clearbox}I don't know anything~{nl}
I mean~ it's not in{nl}
any of the books.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: Oh... I see.{waitkey}Then I'll look into it{nl}
myself. This door{nl}
intrigues me, too.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: It says "Tower of{nl}
Nemesis" - in Greek{nl}
letters.{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: Hey, Kuroori seems{nl}
to know his demons and{nl}
occult stuff, right?{waitkey}{clearbox}Bet he'd be useful. Be good{nl}
to have someone like that{nl}
on our side.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Hm, good thinking.{waitkey}We are indeed ignorant{nl}
of demons right now.{waitkey}{clearbox}Know the foe and know{nl}
yourself, and win every{nl}
battle. The art of war says{waitkey}know your enemy first.{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Ehh~ but, like,{nl}
putting it mildly,{nl}
he's not my type~{waitkey}{clearbox}Ayase says hard pass.{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: That's putting it{nl}
mildly? And his being your{nl}
type is beside the point.{waitkey}{clearbox}Though he does seem{nl}
unreliable, I'll admit.{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Hey hey, what about{nl}
Kirishima? She could{nl}
translate for foreign demons.{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: Now that you mention{nl}
it, she knows that kind of{nl}
thing. Yeah, could be good.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: What are you all{nl}
talking about?{waitkey}{clearbox}I didn't mean to eavesdrop,{nl}
but my name came up, so{nl}
I grew curious.{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: Ah, well, just that{nl}
someone who knows demons{nl}
turned up at the right time.{waitkey}{clearbox}You see......{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: Oh! So that's why the{nl}
school is wrapped in ice.{nl}
How fascinating.{waitkey}{clearbox}I do love tales of Monsters{nl}
and Ghosts, but...{waitkey}{clearbox}for them to keep becoming{nl}
real, one after another...{waitkey}{ret}

Someone must do something,{nl}
and soon.{nl}
{ctl0e:7}{ret}

Elly: OK!{waitkey}{clearbox}To save Ms. Saeko, let's{nl}
search for the "Shards of{nl}
the Devil's Mirror."{waitkey}{ret}
